  "text": "Multilocus sequence typing (MLST) showed that Bifidobacterium animalis is phylogenetically distant from other species of the genus [CITATION_1] . Indeed, strains belonging to B. animalis subsp. lactis are difficult to differentiate due to the high degree of genome identity among strains (99.975%) [CITATION_2] . Proper strain identification is a very valuable trait for both producers and consumers, as close probiotic strains may have different effects on host health, notably at the immunomodulation level [CITATION_3] .",
